==English==

===Etymology===
Named after [[w:John Langdon-Down|John L.H. Langdon-Down]] (1828-1896), an English physician who described it in the late 1800s. The term was first used in 1961.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|sg=[[Down]] [[syndrome]]|-}}

# {{context|teratology}} Condition caused by a [[chromosomal]] [[deficiency]], whereby the patients bear a certain [[resemblance]] to the [[Mongoloid]] race, such as a small head and [[tilt]]ed eyelids.
Also a form of mental retardation.

